message: A painting form the 1500's has no place in a discussion about a clinical term which originated in the 20th century. Caravaggio's painting is attached to the Narcissism article which has historic roots back to the 1500's and prior.

Gasligted is the past tense of gaslight - see dictionary. True compounds of the verb “to light” work this way: you can talk about a “floodlit” stage, because it is lit with floodlights. But “gaslight” does not come from the verb “to light”, meaning “to illuminate”.
